reviewText: It's a film I feel compelled to watch very often. These are characters that I love spending time with, and just enough quirk to satisfy people that need more than just ennui. It's a film I recommend to everyone and am more than willing to sit and watch any time.
it's a slow and steady beautifully melancholic coming of age story.  lovingly shot.
My boyfriend saw this at the Toronto Film Festival and just loved this movie. He says it was great film making!
This movie is a very moving picture about the ennui that follows graduating college. Beautiful and poetic, this movie is truly a modern masterpiece.
pleasant way to spend a couple of hours.
